"{\"paper\": {\"status\": \"map_review\", \"title\": \"Explaining and Suggesting Relatedness in Knowledge Graphs\", \"url\": \"http://disi.unitn.it/~pavel/OM/articles/93660561.pdf\", \"abstract\": \"Knowledge graphs (KGs) are a key ingredient for searching, browsing and knowledge discovery activities. Motivated by the need to harness knowledge available in a variety of KGs, we face the following two problems. First, given a pair of entities defined in some KG, find an explanation of their relatedness. We formalize the notion of relatedness explanation and introduce different criteria to build explanations based on information-theory, diversity and their combinations. Second, given a pair of entities, find other (pairs of) entities sharing a similar relatedness perspective. We describe an implementation of our ideas in a tool, called RECAP, which is based on RDF and SPARQL. We provide an evaluation of RECAP and a comparison with related systems on real-world data.\", \"field\": \"Knowledge graphs; RECAP\", \"rdf\": \"Explaining_and_Sugge_0.rdf\", \"user\": \"matching\"}, \"map_name\": \"Explaining_and_Sugge_1.html\", \"_id\": {\"$oid\": \"5a4f452e180e1115783ec71f\"}, \"annotation\": {\"metrics\": [{\"type\": \"Qualitative\", \"name\": \"knowledge discovery activities_quality\", \"task_name\": {\"name\": \"knowledge discovery activities\"}, \"measure\": \"quality\"}], \"tasks\": [{\"name\": \"Knowledge graphs (KGs)\"}, {\"name\": \"searching\"}, {\"name\": \"browsing\"}, {\"name\": \"knowledge discovery activities\"}, {\"name\": \"harness knowledge available in a variety of KGs\"}, {\"name\": \"find an explanation of their relatedness - relatedness explanation\"}, {\"name\": \"criteria to build explanations based on information-theory, diversity and their combinations\"}, {\"name\": \"find other (pairs of) entities sharing a similar relatedness perspective\"}, {\"name\": \"RECAP\"}, {\"name\": \"RDF\"}, {\"name\": \"SPARQL\"}], \"datasets\": [], \"results\": [{\"value